<p><span class="highlight">Russell Krysiak</span>'s participation in architecture is the latest facet of the body of experience he has gained and maintained as an artist and designer.  Raised in a 'craft' tradition, and maintaining a BFA in Metalsmithing, he has developed and refined skills working also in wood, glass, leather and weaving among other media.  Having completed apprenticeships with artists including Mary Frank and Martin Puryear, Russell continues to pursue the design and fabrication of objects of his own design in his Lomontville studio, and has received both awards and publication of his works.</p>

<p><span class="highlight">Ilene Mark</span> brings a variety of design and management related experiences to the studio.  With a BFA and academic training in Visual Arts, Textile and Fashion design, she has a broad background in the conceptualization and realization of artistic projects.  Having had the opportunity to manage a variety of artists and professionals including Musicians, Composers and Jewelry Designers, Ilene brings extensive experience to the development, administration and realization of projects in the studio.</p>

